\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, stock paste, water and reserved porcini powder and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid."},{"content":"Add bay leaf, rosemary and oregano into mixng bowl and cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Serve bolognaise with cooked pasta of choice and sprinkle with reserved Parmesan cheese before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can make extra dried porcini powder, then store it in a sealable storage container in the pantry for up to 3 months.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","To cook pasta in your Thermomix, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","45m","4 portions"]}